Monokuma | Kev 2021-11-19 14:15:21Z
The jungle grove. A large clearing in the jungle, this large and open space is a good spot for recreational activities like a picnic. Trees around the grove have various fruits like apples and cacao beans, able to be picked. Large stone statues resembling heads also sit in various spots around the grove. This place also has butterflies and bees flying around, with birds nests accompanying them in the trees. Interestingly, the entire place is covered in flowers. They’re all white flowers and sweet smelling. There are 8 statues in the grove, arranged in random locations throughout the open area facing random directions. They seem to have been built here a long time ago as moss is creeping up the side of the stone faces. The stone statues, resembling "moyai" () are all different shapes and sizes as well, with some having distinct facial features such as an enlongated nose or a larger mouth. The heights also vary. However, all of them are easily bigger than all of you, and each of them probably weighs a few thousand pounds. Standing in the circle of heads, surrounded by flowers and wildlife, you can't help but get a grand sense of power from this place. A majestic and large presence hangs in the air. The wind blows at a subtle pace. I call on you to be more than you think you can be.

Who needs rooms, am I right? Not Daisuke!!! Yet. He made his way into the clearing and looked around. Huh. Anyway- He went right the way through the middle of it and then back into the jungle on the other side. They walked slowly to try make as little sound as possible, not wanting to disturb anything, and to also avoid stepping on something. Getting bitten by an angry creature would be a terrible start to a holiday. They eventually stopped under a tree, though, deeming it a good spot to sleep for tonight. The beach would have been a more… responsible choice. But he had had enough of sand in his underwear for today. So he quickly and nimbly climbed up, stopping on a branch thick enough for him to comfortably sit on. Daisuke took his backpack off and hung it off a nearby branch. He then yanked a bunch of vines free and twisted them quickly together to form some sort of rope. They sat down with their back against the trunk and legs going down the branch, using the ‘rope’ to tie themself to it. There! All safe and secure. A very acceptable first night bed. Daisuke fell asleep quickly, looking sort of weird in such a rigid position, but whatever. He slept well uwu
